{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon"

    metadata = {
        description = "The planner network. The runner invokes it at TWO points. (1) kind=episode_start, fired before turn 1 of each new episode: compare the BEST-EVER episode (across all runs) against the LAST (most recent) episode via RunTelemetry select mode — raw filtered steps, no rollups — then REVISE the existing plan in place (WriteEpisodePlan: turn-phased checklist + coordinator strategy summary + per-domain summaries) and log at most 3 fresh trials for the upcoming episode. (2) kind=episode_end, fired on the done=true row: a THIN close-out only — promote this episode's confirmed trials, ResolveTrials, advance_episode. All cross-run analysis and trial planning happen at start, not end. Mid-episode periodic analysis (steps 10..90) lives in the separate watcher network.",
        tags = ["maps", "industry", "consultant", "macro", "advisor"],
        sample_queries = [
            "kind=episode_start episode=4 step=0 cumulative_reward=0 final_reward=null",
            "kind=episode_end episode=3 step=100 cumulative_reward=88120 final_reward=88120"
        ]
    },

    include "config/llm_config.hocon",

    llm_config = ${llm_config},

    max_steps = 4000,
    max_execution_seconds = 1200,

    tools = [
        {
            name = "macro_orchestrator",
            max_message_history = 2,
            function = {
                description = "Front-man router for the planner network. kind=episode_start -> episode_start; kind=episode_end -> episode_end. Does no analysis itself."
            },
            instructions = """
You are the planner network's router. Your input looks like:
"kind=<episode_start|episode_end> episode=<E> step=<S> cumulative_reward=<C> final_reward=<F> [recovery=true doom_reason=<...>] [aborted=<true|false> reason=<...>]".

- If kind=episode_start then call episode_start with inquiry "episode=<E>". If the input carries `recovery=true`, append it plus
  the `doom_reason=<...>` VERBATIM to that inquiry (e.g. "episode=4 recovery=true doom_reason=<...>") so the planner refines the
  restored champion instead of replanning fresh. Relay its one-line status verbatim.
- If kind=episode_end then call episode_end(episode=<E>, cumulative_reward=<C>, aborted=<the flag, default false>). Relay its
  one-line recap verbatim.

ERROR HANDLING: if any tool call or downstream agent returns an error, STOP and reply with `ERROR: <the verbatim error text>`.
Never swallow, paraphrase, retry silently, or continue past it.
""",
            middleware = [ {"class": "langchain_anthropic.middleware.AnthropicPromptCachingMiddleware", "args": {"ttl": "1h"}} ],
            tools = ["episode_start", "episode_end"]
        },

        {
            name = "episode_start",
            max_message_history = 2,
            function = ${aaosa_call} {
                description = "Episode-start planner (kind=episode_start). Analyzes best-vs-last, seeds up to 3 macro trials directly (LogTrial), and REVISES the existing plan in place (WriteEpisodePlan: checklist + coordinator strategy summary + per-domain summaries) — keeping what works, changing only what underperformed. Input: episode=<E> [recovery=true doom_reason=<...>]."
            },
            instructions = """
You plan the UPCOMING episode (input: episode=<E>). Never hallucinate — cite an episode + step/metric for every claim.
Flow: ANALYZE -> READ prior outcomes -> DECIDE up to 3 TRIALS -> LOG them (LogTrial) -> REVISE the existing PLAN around them.

RECOVERY MODE: if the input carries `recovery=true`, the last episode doomed and the playbooks already hold the restored
champion — refine that champion with new trial strategies, and read the doomed last episode only as what-to-avoid (per
`doom_reason`), never as a model.

Procedure:
1. ANALYZE — first state_read('maps_game_docs') for the game rules. Then call RunTelemetry(select='best_and_last') which gives
   the best-ever and last episodes as raw per-step rows. Compare them move-by-move: where the best pulled ahead and the last
   regressed — build-out pace, research timing, ride/shop placement, staff hiring, ride/shop switches, rejections.
   The rows also carry per-step park_rating — use it to work out what keeps the rating HIGH which drives guest attendance.
   Try to pinpoint strategy trials that would BEAT the current best.
2. The best run is your FLOOR: when even the best run falls far short of the goal, lightly tuning it is not enough. Look for a
   STRUCTURAL blocker holding every run back rather than execution noise. Find it from the data yourself: a metric that never
   moves, an action that never fires or never runs long enough to complete, a resource that never accumulates enough to matter?
   Make removing that blocker the spine of the plan.
3. READ the strategies that have already been tried and CANNOT BE USED AGAIN — state_read('trial_strategies_outcome') for
   confirmed/learned AND falsified strategies + the last close-out's PRIORITY/DIRECTION steer. Never re-suggest any of it.
4. Based on the above analysis, decide up to 3 TRIAL strategies — broad, park-wide bets for the whole episode, each in a
   DIFFERENT domain, aimed at $1M park_value, with at least one aimed at the structural blocker from step 2. Also be CREATIVE:
   test bold, untried directions you believe could work. Each must be NEW (not an active trial, learned rule, or falsified
   idea) and falsifiable — a concrete metric + direction + window. (The watcher network adds its own finer trials mid-episode.)
5. Call ActiveTrials(trial_origin='macro') for any carried over from a prior episode, compare against your new candidates and
   keep only the strongest — never two trials in one domain. Call LogTrial once per kept trial:
   new_text = a general one-sentence imperative (no observed values or examples), step_start='1'.
6. REVISE THE PLAN — edit the existing one, do NOT rebuild it from scratch. Read the current plan as your BASE:
   state_read('episode_checklist') for the current turn-phased checklist, state_read('playbook_coordinator') for its strategy
   summary, and state_read each 'playbook_<domain>' for its summary. Keep the parts the data shows are working, and change only
   the phases the last episode underperformed plus whatever the new trials target. Then call
   WriteEpisodePlan(checklist_items, strategy_summary, playbook_summaries) with the edited text — it must exercise the seeded
   trials and obey the game rules. The three fields:
   - checklist_items: the full turns-1..100 plan, one "turns A-B: <goal>" line per phase.
   - strategy_summary: the coordinator's brief — 6-8 phases, each with (a) its goal, (b) the moves in order, (c) end-of-phase
     targets on the key metrics toward the $1M goal — ending with a short "failure modes to avoid" list.
   - playbook_summaries: a 4-5 line summary PER domain, but pass ONLY the domains whose guidance changes this episode; omit the
     rest and their current summary stays untouched.
7. Return ONE terse status line, e.g. "episode_started: plan written, <N> trials seeded".

ERROR HANDLING: if any tool call or downstream agent returns an error, STOP and reply with `ERROR: <the verbatim error text>`.
Never swallow, paraphrase, retry silently, or continue past it.
""",
            middleware = [
                {"class": "middleware.trim_history_middleware.TrimHistoryMiddleware", "args": {}},
                {"class": "langchain_anthropic.middleware.AnthropicPromptCachingMiddleware", "args": {"ttl": "1h"}}
            ],
            tools = ["RunTelemetry", "state_read", "ActiveTrials", "LogTrial", "WriteEpisodePlan"]
        },

        {
            name = "episode_end",
            max_message_history = 2,
            function = ${aaosa_call} {
                description = "Episode-end close-out (kind=episode_end). Evaluates this episode's trials, promotes confirmed ones (or falsifies ALL if aborted), ResolveTrials, then advance_episode. Inputs: episode, cumulative_reward, aborted."
            },
            instructions = """
You run the end-of-episode close-out and are the sole writer of the playbook learned-rule lines. Inputs: episode=<E>,
cumulative_reward=<C> (this episode's final), aborted (default false). Never hallucinate; cite a step/metric from telemetry. All
writes go through the tools.

Procedure:
1. Read your context (call whenever needed):
   - state_read('last_reward'): the PRIOR episode's final reward if present, else 0.
   - ActiveTrials(): the trials you must evaluate this close-out.
   - EpisodeTelemetry(): this episode's per-step record (the evidence you score the trials against).
2. EVALUATE each active trial against telemetry.steps in its window — decide whether the trial's intended move actually fired by
   READING THE RUN itself: the per-step rows in EpisodeTelemetry().steps (each carries action/subtype/subclass/price/x/y +
   the metrics) and EpisodeTelemetry().rejections. Do NOT rely on the pre-digested `applied` list; judge from what the run shows.
   Then score the trial:
   success met + failure not tripped => confirmed; failure tripped => falsified; neither => inconclusive.
   ABORT OVERRIDE: if aborted=true, promote NOTHING and mark EVERY active trial falsified (note 'run aborted as doomed').
3. PROMOTE each confirmed trial: PromoteTrial(domain, edit_type='add_line', new_text=<general imperative — one sentence, no
   episode numbers, step counts, or observed values>, episode=<E>, section='Learned rules (promoted from prior runs)'). Append
   only — never replace or remove existing lines.
4. ResolveTrials(episode=<E>, report=<per-trial [{trial_id, domain, outcome, note}]>). Removes confirmed/falsified + ALL micro
   trials (episode-scoped); keeps macro not_applied/inconclusive to carry forward.
5. advance_episode(final_reward=<C>, episode=<E>, outcome_summary=<3-6 bullets: CONFIRMED rule+domain, FALSIFIED what+why,
   INCONCLUSIVE not-testable-do-not-re-propose; if aborted, say the run was cut short as doomed and its trials rejected>).
6. Return ONE short line: "<N> promoted, <M> falsified, final=<C>" (note if the run was aborted). This is injected into the next
   episode's turn-1 prompt, so keep it tight.

ERROR HANDLING: if any tool call or downstream agent returns an error, STOP and reply with `ERROR: <the verbatim error text>`.
Never swallow, paraphrase, retry silently, or continue past it.
""",
            middleware = [
                {"class": "middleware.trim_history_middleware.TrimHistoryMiddleware", "args": {}},
                {"class": "langchain_anthropic.middleware.AnthropicPromptCachingMiddleware", "args": {"ttl": "1h"}}
            ],
            tools = ["state_read", "EpisodeTelemetry", "ActiveTrials", "PromoteTrial", "ResolveTrials", "advance_episode"]
        },

        {
            name = "advance_episode",
            class = "coded_tools.advance_episode.AdvanceEpisode",
            function = {
                description = "End-of-episode bookkeeping: persists reward, clears the observation cache, inserts LLM outcome_summary under '## Episode Summaries' in the outcome ledger, and trims old raw OUTCOME lines. Trial strategies/criteria cleanup happens at episode START via SeedPlaybooks (runner).",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        final_reward = {
                            type = "float",
                            description = "This episode's cumulative_reward; written to last_reward.md."
                        },
                        episode = {
                            type = "int",
                            description = "Current episode number; used to age out stale trials and tag the summary."
                        },
                        outcome_summary = {
                            type = "string",
                            description = "LLM-crafted concise summary of this episode's trial outcomes: what was confirmed (rule + domain), what was falsified (rule + why), what was inconclusive and why, plus the run-level trend/priority. Inserted under '## Episode Summaries' in trial_strategies_outcome.md so the next episode_start pass knows what NOT to re-propose."
                        }
                    },
                    required = ["final_reward", "episode"]
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "RunTelemetry",
            class = "coded_tools.run_telemetry.RunTelemetry",
            function = {
                description = "SELECT mode (select='best_and_last') — what the start analyst uses: the best-ever episode (across all runs) + the last episode, as RAW filtered per-step rows (no rollups; read the moves directly). RUNS mode (num_runs, default 5): per-run + per-episode rollups for the N most recent runs plus a cross-run rollup. EPISODE mode (default): per-episode rollups for the current run plus a run rollup, including reward_bands (the compounding curve: avg reward/step in the 1-25/26-50/51-75/76-100 step bands).",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        select = { type = "string", description = "SELECT mode: pass 'best_and_last' to get the best-ever episode + the last episode as raw filtered steps (what the start analyst uses)." }
                        num_runs = { type = "int", description = "RUNS mode: analyze the N most recent runs (current + prior). Default 5." }
                        scope = { type = "string", description = "Optional explicit mode: 'select', 'runs', or 'episodes'. Usually leave unset — select/num_runs select the mode." }
                        from_episode = { type = "int", description = "EPISODE mode only: include episodes >= this. Omit for the whole current run." }
                        max_episodes = { type = "int", description = "EPISODE mode only: keep only the most recent N episodes (after from_episode). Omit for all." }
                    }
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "WriteEpisodePlan",
            class = "coded_tools.write_episode_plan.WriteEpisodePlan",
            function = {
                description = "Persist the start-of-episode plan: the turn-phased checklist (episode_checklist.md -> current_phase), the coordinator strategy-summary block (playbook_coordinator.md, read every turn), and optional per-domain summary blocks in each specialist playbook (rides/shops/staff/research/layout/survey). All overwritten each episode.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        checklist_items = {
                            type = "array",
                            items = { type = "string" },
                            description = "The full turn-phased plan, one literal 'turns A-B: <goal>' line per item, ordered by turn, covering turns 1..100."
                        }
                        strategy_summary = {
                            type = "string",
                            description = "Freeform prose brief — the best way to go about this episode (the how/why behind the checklist) — written into playbook_coordinator for the strategy_coordinator."
                        }
                        playbook_summaries = {
                            type = "object",
                            description = "Optional per-domain summaries. Keys are any of 'rides','shops','staff','research','layout','survey'; each value is a 4-5 line summary of how THAT specialist should play THIS episode (derived from the best/last comparison), written to the top of that specialist's playbook and read by it every consultation. Omit a domain to leave its current summary unchanged.",
                            properties = {
                                rides    = { type = "string", description = "4-5 line summary for rides_manager this episode." }
                                shops    = { type = "string", description = "4-5 line summary for shops_manager this episode." }
                                staff    = { type = "string", description = "4-5 line summary for staffing_manager this episode." }
                                research = { type = "string", description = "4-5 line summary for research_lead this episode." }
                                layout   = { type = "string", description = "4-5 line summary for park_layout_planner this episode." }
                                survey   = { type = "string", description = "4-5 line summary for guest_analyst this episode." }
                            }
                        }
                    }
                    required = ["checklist_items", "strategy_summary"]
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "EpisodeTelemetry",
            class = "coded_tools.episode_telemetry.EpisodeTelemetry",
            function = {
                description = "Per-step factual record for ONE episode from the deterministic run.jsonl (steps, applied, rejections, rollup; exists=false if no rows yet). Each step carries the action args + metrics. To decide whether a trial's intended move fired, READ `steps` and `rejections`, NOT the lossy `applied` digest; use the per-step reward/value/rating deltas for success/failure. `rejections` lists every action the sim REFUSED (booked as a wait with the original rejected_action + error) — a repeated rejected_action with the same error is a prime trial target.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        episode   = { type = "int", description = "Episode number to read. Omit to use the latest episode present in the log." }
                        from_step = { type = "int", description = "Only return steps >= this (mid-episode tail). Omit for the full episode." }
                    }
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "LogTrial",
            class = "coded_tools.log_trial.LogTrial",
            function = {
                description = "Mint a collision-free trial_id and append the matching pair of lines to trial_strategies (the one-line rule) and trial_strategies_criteria (the metadata + success/failure criteria). Use this for EVERY new trial; never count ids or hand-format the criteria line yourself. (origin is bound to this network by config — you do NOT pass it.)",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        episode           = { type = "int", description = "Current episode number." }
                        step_start        = { type = "string",  description = "Step at which the trial activates (as a string), or the literal 'end_of_episode'." }
                        domain            = { type = "string",  description = "One of: rides, shops, staff, research, layout, survey, coordinator." }
                        section           = { type = "string",  description = "Target playbook section header (or 'new')." }
                        edit_type         = { type = "string",  description = "'add_line' or 'replace_line'." }
                        new_text          = { type = "string",  description = "The one-line rule to add/replace (no rationale or metrics embedded)." }
                        find_text         = { type = "string",  description = "replace_line only: the exact existing playbook line to replace." }
                        rationale         = { type = "string",  description = "One sentence citing step(s) / metric delta." }
                        success_criterion = { type = "string",  description = "Observable metric + direction + evaluation window (turns; fits in the fixed 100-step episode)." }
                        failure_criterion = { type = "string",  description = "Observable metric that would falsify the trial." }
                    }
                    required = ["episode", "step_start", "domain", "section", "edit_type", "new_text", "rationale", "success_criterion", "failure_criterion"]
                }
            }
            args = { origin = "macro" }
        },

        {
            name = "ActiveTrials",
            class = "coded_tools.active_trials.ActiveTrials",
            function = {
                description = "Return the active trials joined across trial_strategies (rule body) and trial_strategies_criteria (metadata), optionally filtered by domain and/or trial_origin ('micro'|'macro').",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        domain = { type = "string", description = "Filter to one domain. Omit for all domains." }
                        trial_origin = { type = "string", description = "Filter to 'micro' or 'macro'. Omit for both. (Named trial_origin, NOT origin — 'origin' is a reserved framework-injected field.)" }
                    }
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "ResolveTrials",
            class = "coded_tools.resolve_trials.ResolveTrials",
            function = {
                description = "Apply the curator's per-trial report at episode end: remove confirmed/falsified trials from trial_strategies + trial_strategies_criteria, keep not_applied/inconclusive (and any unreported active trial, as inconclusive note='no_report'), and append an OUTCOME line for every active trial to trial_strategies_outcome.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        episode = { type = "int", description = "Current episode number." }
                        report  = { type = "string", description = "JSON list of the curator's per-trial objects: [{trial_id, domain, outcome, note}], outcome in confirmed/falsified/not_applied/inconclusive." }
                    }
                    required = ["episode", "report"]
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "PromoteTrial",
            class = "coded_tools.promote_trial.PromoteTrial",
            function = {
                description = "Apply ONE confirmed trial's edit to playbook_<domain>.md, tagging the new line '(learned ep<N>)'. add_line appends at end (section 'end'/'new'/empty) or inserts after the named section header; replace_line replaces the unique find_text. On a successful live edit the learned line is also mirrored into the config seed (config_files/<domain>_strategy.md) under a '## Learned rules' section so it survives fresh runs.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        domain    = { type = "string",  description = "rides/shops/staff/research/layout/survey/coordinator." }
                        edit_type = { type = "string",  description = "'add_line' or 'replace_line'." }
                        new_text  = { type = "string",  description = "The rule line to add/replace (without the learned tag)." }
                        episode   = { type = "int", description = "Episode number for the '(learned ep<N>)' tag." }
                        section   = { type = "string",  description = "add_line: section header to insert after, or 'end'/'new' to append." }
                        find_text = { type = "string",  description = "replace_line: the exact existing playbook line to replace." }
                    }
                    required = ["domain", "edit_type", "new_text", "episode"]
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "state_read",
            class = "coded_tools.state_read.StateRead",
            function = {
                description = "Read a file by its logical name from the operator-configured name_map.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        name = { type = "string", description = "Logical name." }
                    },
                    required = ["name"]
                }
            },
            args = {
                name_map = {
                    trial_strategies            = "coded_tools/state/trial_strategies.md"
                    trial_strategies_criteria   = "coded_tools/state/trial_strategies_criteria.md"
                    trial_strategies_outcome    = "coded_tools/state/trial_strategies_outcome.md"
                    last_reward                 = "coded_tools/state/last_reward.md"
                    playbook_coordinator        = "coded_tools/state/playbook_coordinator.md"
                    playbook_rides              = "coded_tools/state/playbook_rides.md"
                    playbook_shops              = "coded_tools/state/playbook_shops.md"
                    playbook_staff              = "coded_tools/state/playbook_staff.md"
                    playbook_research           = "coded_tools/state/playbook_research.md"
                    playbook_layout             = "coded_tools/state/playbook_layout.md"
                    playbook_survey             = "coded_tools/state/playbook_survey.md"
                    episode_checklist           = "coded_tools/state/episode_checklist.md"
                    economics_rides             = "coded_tools/config_files/rides_economics.md"
                    economics_shops             = "coded_tools/config_files/shops_economics.md"
                    economics_staff             = "coded_tools/config_files/staff_economics.md"
                    economics_research          = "coded_tools/config_files/research_economics.md"
                    maps_game_docs              = "coded_tools/config_files/maps_game_docs.md"
                    seed_playbook_coordinator   = "coded_tools/config_files/coordinator_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_rides         = "coded_tools/config_files/rides_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_shops         = "coded_tools/config_files/shops_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_staff         = "coded_tools/config_files/staff_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_research      = "coded_tools/config_files/research_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_layout        = "coded_tools/config_files/layout_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_survey        = "coded_tools/config_files/survey_strategy.md"
                }
            }
        },
    ]
}
